I have a role named Test_role2 with the following indices/index patterns:

[
  "cost*",
  ".watcher-history-*",
  "client_status",
  "prod:traces-apm*,prod:logs-apm*,prod:metrics-apm*",
  "qa:traces-apm*,qa:logs-apm*,qa:metrics-apm*",
  "dev:traces-apm*,dev:logs-apm*,dev:metrics-apm*,dev:apm-*",
  "prod:filebeat-*",
  "prod:filebeat-*-inframon-*",
  "qa:metricbeat-*",
  "dev:metricbeat-*-mt-*-cw",
  "*:metricbeat-*-mt-*"
]

When I run the script, I see that the local equivalent of the remote indices are being added multiple times are I run the script multiple times.

As you may notice, sometimes, a remote index could look like "qa:metricbeat-*", and sometimes it looks like the pattern "prod:traces-apm*,prod:logs-apm*,prod:metrics-apm*".

When it looks like "qa:metricbeat-*" or similar pattern, a local index/index pattern "metricbeat-*" should be added. When the pattern is something like "prod:traces-apm*,prod:logs-apm*,prod:metrics-apm*", this should be added: "traces-apm*,logs-apm*,metrics-apm*".

Also, if the local index equivalent of an index or index pattern is already added to the role. For example, if I have something like "qa:metricbeat-*", and "metricbeat-*" was already updated, and I run the script, it should not re-add another "metricbeat-*"
